  <!-- THE WIRRAL APPLIANCE PROBLEM, UNIQUE SECTION -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pf-section-label">WIRRAL LANDLORD KNOWLEDGE</span>
      <h2>Your Wirral CP12 Must Cover Every Gas Appliance. Not Just the Boiler.</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">This is the most common compliance mistake on the Wirral. A gas safety certificate that covers only the boiler and not the gas fire in the living room is legally incomplete. Here is what needs to be on your certificate.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-red">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Back Boilers and Gas Fires in CH41, CH42 and CH44</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 0.75rem;line-height:1.65;">The Victorian and Edwardian terraces of Birkenhead, Rock Ferry and Wallasey have a high proportion of gas fires in living rooms, many connected to back boilers, others as standalone appliances. The Gas Safety Regulations 1998 are explicit: every gas appliance in the rental property must be inspected individually and recorded on the CP12. A landlord with a Birkenhead terrace that has a back boiler and a gas fire in the living room cannot legally produce a complete CP12 that covers only the boiler.</p>
          <div style="background:#fef2f2;border:1px solid #fecaca;border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:0.75rem 1rem;">
            <p style="font-size:0.88rem;color:#7f1d1d;margin:0;font-weight:600;">If your CP12 lists only the boiler but your property also has a gas fire, you may not be legally compliant even if you have a current certificate. We check every gas appliance in the property in a single visit, all on the same certificate.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Gas Hobs and Cookers in Rental Properties</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">If the landlord supplies a gas hob, gas cooker or gas range as part of the rental property, these must also be included on the CP12. The test is whether the appliance was supplied by the landlord as part of the tenancy. If the tenant brought it themselves, it is the tenant's responsibility. If it was in the property when they moved in, it is yours. We check all landlord-supplied gas appliances in a single visit at £10 per additional appliance beyond the first.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">What We Check in a Single Wirral Visit</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">We check every gas appliance in your Wirral rental property, boiler, back boiler, gas fires, gas hobs, gas cookers, individually. Each appliance is recorded separately on the CP12 with its location, the checks carried out and the result. One visit covers the whole property, one certificate covers everything, and both the landlord and tenant receive the same digital document by email the same day.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- LEGAL OBLIGATIONS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Wirral Landlords. This Is a Legal Requirement.</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Under the <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safety (Installation and Use) Regulations 1998</a>, every Wirral landlord must hold a valid CP12 for every rental property containing gas appliances. Non-compliance carries serious legal and financial consequences.</p>

      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">1</div>
          <div><strong>Fines up to £6,000 per Wirral property</strong><p>The <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Health and Safety Executive</a> and Wirral Metropolitan Borough Council both enforce gas safety compliance. A single non-compliant Wirral property can result in a fine of up to £6,000. Criminal prosecution and imprisonment are possible in serious cases. A CP12 costs £80.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">2</div>
          <div><strong>A lapsed CP12 can block a Section 21 notice</strong><p>A landlord who has not provided a valid gas safety certificate to their tenant may be unable to serve a valid Section 21 notice to regain possession. Courts have ruled that CP12 compliance is a legal prerequisite for a valid Section 21. A lapsed or unserved certificate can prevent eviction proceedings entirely on Wirral properties.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">3</div>
          <div><strong>Certificate must be provided to tenants within 28 days</strong><p>You must provide a copy of the valid CP12 to existing tenants within 28 days of issue. New tenants must receive a copy before they move in. We email the digital certificate the same day so you can forward it to Wirral tenants immediately.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">4</div>
          <div><strong>Required for Wirral Council HMO licensing</strong><p>A valid CP12 is a mandatory requirement for any Wirral Metropolitan Borough Council HMO licence. Without it your HMO licence application will not be processed. Wirral Council's housing enforcement team actively inspect HMO properties across Birkenhead, Wallasey and Bebington. A lapsed CP12 puts your licence at risk.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">5</div>
          <div><strong>Records must be kept for two years</strong><p>Landlords must keep a record of the gas safety inspection for a minimum of two years. We email the digital certificate the same day, creating a permanent timestamped record. We recommend one folder per Wirral property with all annual certificates stored chronologically.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">6</div>
          <div><strong>Certificate must be renewed every 12 months</strong><p>A CP12 is valid for 12 months from the date of inspection. If renewed between 10 and 12 months after the previous one, the new certificate runs from the expiry date of the old one, preserving the full 12 months without any gap. We add all Wirral landlords to our annual reminder list so your certificate never lapses.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WHAT IS CHECKED -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What Our Gas Safe Engineers Check at Your Wirral Property</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Every gas appliance in the property inspected individually. The inspection takes 30 to 45 minutes for a single appliance, longer if back boilers or gas fires are also present.</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Gas supply pressure and flow rate</strong><p>Gas supply pressure tested at the meter and at each appliance. Low pressure or restricted flow can cause appliances to operate unsafely.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Gas leak check</strong><p>All pipework and appliance connections tested for gas leaks using calibrated detection equipment. Any leak classified under the Gas Industry Unsafe Situations Procedure.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Flue integrity and combustion products</strong><p>All flues tested for integrity, correct sealing and safe discharge. Back boilers and open-flue gas fires receive combustion spillage testing specific to open-flue appliances.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Ventilation adequacy</strong><p>All gas appliances checked for adequate ventilation. Blocked or inadequate ventilation is a common cause of incomplete combustion and carbon monoxide risk, particularly in older Birkenhead and Wallasey terraces.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Safety device operation</strong><p>All appliance safety devices tested individually. Each must demonstrate correct operation before the appliance can pass the inspection.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Signs of incomplete combustion</strong><p>Checked for staining, sooting or carbon deposits around appliances. Particularly important for gas fires and back boilers where these signs are more common than on sealed combi boilers.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>All gas appliances in the property</strong><p>Every gas appliance inspected individually, boiler, back boiler, gas fires, gas hobs, cookers. All recorded separately on the CP12.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>CP12 certificate issued and emailed same day</strong><p>Digital CP12 emailed the same day. Includes the engineer's Gas Safe registration number, inspection date and result for every appliance checked.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


